The Minister of Aviation under Goodluck Jonathan administration, Femi Fani-Kayode has reacted to the death of pastor T B Joshua. It was gathered that the popular cleric died on Saturday after a church program. “The passing of my brother TB Joshua saddens me deeply. At 3.00 am this morning I was told by one of his daughters that this was fake news & I tweeted as much.” “Sadly I was misled. 5 minutes ago the same person called me & confirmed the story. @GazetteNGR was right & I am in pain.” READ ALSO: Ten things you should know about Prophet TB Joshua Naija News had earlier reported that the death of the founder of Synagogue Church of All Nations, Pastor TB Joshua has been confirmed by the church. The cleric who popularly known as T B Joshua died at the age of 57.